I was able to reproduce it with the following program:

#include <stdlib.h>

int main(int argc, char **argv)
{
        int i;


        for (i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
                void * ptr = malloc(32);
                sleep(1);
                free(ptr);
        }

//      exit(0);
        return (0);
}


My dtrace invocation was:
sudo dtrace -c ./malloc -n 'pid$target::malloc:entry { ustack(); }
